<br>
This is the first time I've done a thread where I have more than one update on the picture, and I think it's been great for me aswell. If I had just posted one picture, done the changes I received from others and then considered it done, I wouldn't have gotten this far with the picture. As you said yourself, it's gone from one level up to another, and a third, etc <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I'm just hoping that I won't lose my interest in this picture before the b&amp;w part is finished, atleast. It'd be great to get the picture colored, too, but it all depends on whether I feel inspired or not. Here's to hoping I will <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
As for the boy, do you think bringing his hair down some (and thus making his forehead smaller) would make him look better?<br>
<br>
The day / night lighting idea is an excellent one, and I'll give it consideration should I proceed with coloring the image. The problem is that the picture has been shadowed according to one big lightsource (off the right edge of the image). We'd have to assume that both the sun and the moon (which would be lighting different parts of the image) were situated in the same general direction. That's possible, right? In any case, it's a good idea.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the c&amp;c! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
kopitz,<br>
<br>
As I think I said in one of my earlier posts, I do a LOT of really crappy stuff compared to the &quot;good stuff&quot;. I haven't done much recently since this picture has been all I've worked on whenever I've felt like drawing, but once this is done I suspect I'll hit a streak of uglyness <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
My plans for the picture, apart from fixing things here and there, doesn't include much added content. In that sense if I add some kind of texture to the ground or whatnot, it'll be done in the coloring phase. I'm not actually even sure how I should color this piece.. I've been thinking about really simple flat colors, with minimal shading to make things look round where applicable.<br>
<br>
If I proceed with coloring / shading, it'll bring in deeper shadows and better highlights in some parts, so that'll probably fix your issue with contrast (if I color this). This is why it would be great to get this one colored - I'm sure colors would add a lot more definition and make it easier to set different &quot;objects&quot; in the image apart.<br>
<br>
I'm glad the lips are finally to your liking <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
And thanks for your comments! <p><hr><b>Want to color my lineart?</b> Otherwise alter something I've created? Read my <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujspuonti.showPublicProfile?language=EN"><b>profile</b></a> for further information before proceeding!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usyphernz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syphernz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/12/02 4:09:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7034.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: update 8</span><hr size=1> With the Boys forehead -I think bringing the hair down would accomplish the effect of making him look younger - I'm not 100% certain of anatomical rules here or anything, but I am certain that I have read somewhere about a rule of thirds or something, to make a person look cute/young that forehead should be about 1/3 the size of the face???? The boys forehead take up about half.<br>
<br>
With the lighting effects, there should be no worries with having the same direction of the lighting, but the types of lighting are quite different anyway - Moonlight is softer and more luminescent, and an cool blue tint could be applied to the picture, whereas sunlight could be more radiant, abet sharper shadows, and a dry, warm yellow or red tint could be applied.<br>
<br>
The other thought I had about the passage of time would be indicating spring in the earlier version, and autumn in the later. This would be more tricky, cause you would only have the trunk of the tree and the grass to represent spring, and there are no leaves on the top of the tree, but I guess it could be done with the addition of a few daisy in the bottom, and a falling leaf or two in the background. I don't know, though - it could be too disjointed on one tree - I think lighting would be enough  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uanisource.showPublicProfile?language=EN>anisource</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img2.ranchoweb.com/images/anisource/smileywarz.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/12/02 6:39:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7034.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://img2.ranchoweb.com/images/anisource/chewy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Yakusoku&quot; (~142k b&amp;w, updated eight times</span><hr size=1> You have a very nice pic going here. I agree that bringing the boys hair down over the forhead more would make him look younger but i also have some other comments. The guy's hand (the one that is on his chest) has something wrong with it, i cant quite figure out what but i think the ring finger might be a little short along with the others. If you look at your hand, i think the ring finger is slightly longer than the index finger or at least the same length, you have it drawn a little shorter. That is very nit picky i know but it was bugging me for some reason. Anyway, i cant wait to see the finished product if the in-progress one already looks this good. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ima